1177:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** /*
1178:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** The TLSF block information provides us with enough information to
1179:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** provide a reasonably intelligent implementation of realloc, growing or
1180:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** shrinking the currently allocated block as required.
1181:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** **
1182:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** This routine handles the somewhat esoteric edge cases of realloc:
1183:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** - a non-zero size with a null pointer will behave like malloc
1184:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** - a zero size with a non-null pointer will behave like free
1185:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** - a request that cannot be satisfied will leave the original buffer
1186:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** **   untouched
1187:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** ** - an extended buffer size will leave the newly-allocated area with
1188:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** **   contents undefined
1189:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/stdlib/builtin/lv_tlsf.c **** */
